Run on Startup (Windows)
Option 1: Add to Startup Folder
Press Win + R, type shell:startup, and hit Enter.

This opens the Startup folder.

Create a shortcut here:

Right-click â†’ New â†’ Shortcut

Point it to your Python script with the interpreter:

C:\Path\To\python.exe C:\Scripts\battery_notify.py
Name it something like Battery Notifier.

âœ… This will start the script every time your PC boots.

ðŸš€ Optional (Run in Background on Boot Silently)
If you want it to run silently in the background, turn the script into an .exe:

pip install pyinstaller
pyinstaller --noconsole --onefile battery_notify.py
Then:

Place the generated .exe in the startup folder.

It will run silently at login without opening a terminal window.